                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13682127" author="mduerig" created="Thu, 13 Jun 2013 11:18:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Test case: &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/r1492622&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/r1492622&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13682587" author="mreutegg" created="Thu, 13 Jun 2013 19:18:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The problem is with the MicroKernelImpl.diff(), which returns an incorrect JSOP when KernelNodeStore requests a diff with depth 0. It may happen that MicroKernelImpl.diff() returns a deeper diff than requested.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13682621" author="mreutegg" created="Thu, 13 Jun 2013 19:44:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Changed the KernelNodeStoreTest into a parametrized test. The test is now called NodeStoreTest and runs with MicroKernelImpl, SegmentMK and MongoMK. All of them run in memory.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-872&quot; title=&quot;NodeStoreTest diff failures with MongoMK&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-872&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OAK-872&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for some know issues with MongoMK. Currently skipped with JUnit Assume mechanics.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;svn revision: &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/r1492831&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/r1492831&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13682623" author="mreutegg" created="Thu, 13 Jun 2013 19:45:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Updated summary. This is not related to hidden items.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13683095" author="jukkaz" created="Fri, 14 Jun 2013 04:55:38 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;The test is now called NodeStoreTest and runs with MicroKernelImpl, SegmentMK and MongoMK. All of them run in memory.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Nice!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13772740" author="alex.parvulescu" created="Fri, 20 Sep 2013 07:01:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bulk close for the 0.9 release&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
